  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6560 sitting directly in the heart of massive negative gamma concentration (-36.6B at 6560, -47B at 6550), dealers are being forced to buy this dip aggressively as their short gamma positions demand flow-following hedging. The recent wall break and GEX surge events signal dealers are scrambling to adjust hedges, creating amplified buying pressure that should support any bounce attempt toward the 6600 positive gamma ceiling where they'll flip to selling. Watch 6550 as the critical support - a break below triggers even heavier dealer buying, while a move toward 6600 faces increasing dealer resistance.\n\n**Bottom line:** Dealers are buying the dip hard here, expect a choppy but supported bounce toward 6600.",
